Personal Data We Collect
We collect certain “personal information” and “personal data” as defined by the California Consumer Privacy Act, amended by the California Privacy Rights Act(“CCPA”); the Colorado Privacy Act; the Connecticut Act Concerning Personal Data Privacy and Online Monitoring; the Utah Consumer Privacy Act; and the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (collectively the “U.S. Privacy Laws”) and as listed in the section of the main body of the Privacy Policy titled “What Personal Data Do We Collect About You?” and have done so within the past 12 months.
Personal Data does not include: (a) publicly available information, including information made available from government records; or (b) deidentified information or aggregate consumer information. To the extent that we collect any deidentified information (as defined under U.S. Privacy Laws), we maintain it in deidentified form and do not attempt to reidentify it.
We obtain the categories of Personal Data listed in the “What Personal Data Do We Collect About You?” section above from the following categories of sources:
•
Directly from you
•
Indirectly when you use our services (e.g., via your web browser or device, or via cookies)
•
From Third-Party Services (e.g., Facebook or Twitter)
•
From Integration Partners (e.g., when you use our Services through another app or website, such as Snapchat, TikTok or Twitter)
Use of Personal Data
We may use the Personal Data we collect about you for the following purposes:
•
To Improve, understand, personalize, and operate our Services
•
To Promote the safety, integrity, and security of our Services
•
To Communicate with you
•
To Perform other business purposes
Disclosing Personal Information
We do not “sell” or “share” your Personal Data, as those terms are defined under U.S. Privacy Laws, nor have we “sold” or “shared” your Personal Data in the past 12 months.  We disclose Personal Data with the third parties and for the purposes listed in the section of the main body of the Privacy Policy titled “How, and With Whom, Is My Personal Data Disclosed?” and have done so within the past 12 months. In particular, over the past 12 months we have collected and disclosed:
Identifiers (such as name, IP address, and email address) with service providers that provide cloud computing, analytics, performance and availability monitoring, content moderation services, email marketing and messaging notification services, and with Third-Party Services that you used or otherwise interacted with.
•
Internet and electronic network activity information (such as your interaction with our Services and related log data) with service providers that provide cloud computing, analytics, performance and availability monitoring, content moderation services, and with Third-Party Services that you used or otherwise interacted with.
•
Geolocation data with service providers that provide cloud computing, analytics, performance and availability monitoring and content moderation services, and with Third-Party Services that you used or otherwise interacted with.
Rights
Depending on where you live and subject to certain exceptions, you may have rights in relation to your Personal Data, as outlined below.
• Right to Access/Know:
You may request more information about the Personal Data we collect, use, or disclose, and request a copy of such Personal Data by emailing us at
support@giphy.com
. You can also access some of your Personal Data by logging on to your Account.
• Right to Correct
: You may request that we correct inaccurate Personal Data that we maintain about you. You can make this request by emailing us at
support@giphy.com
. You can also access and correct some of your Personal Data by logging on to your Account.
• Right to Request Deletion:
You may request that we delete the Personal Data that we have collected from you by emailing us at
support@giphy.com
. If you request that we delete your Personal Data, you may no longer be able to use our Services.
• Right to Non-Discrimination:
We will not discriminate against you for exercising your privacy rights under the U.S. Privacy Laws.
To protect your Personal Data, we may need to verify your identity before processing your request to exercise your rights. In some cases, we may need to collect additional Personal Data to verify your identity, such as a government-issued ID.
Under the U.S. Privacy Laws, you may exercise these rights yourself or you may designate an authorized agent to make these requests on your behalf. We may request that your authorized agent have written permission from you to make requests on your behalf and may need to verify your authorized agent’s identity.
To submit a request to exercise your rights, and as applicable, to appeal a consumer rights action, please email us at
support@giphy.com
.
If you have questions about this section or how to exercise your rights, please contact us by emailing
support@giphy.com
.
